pen cqcqcq=rgb(0.75,0.75,0.75);

/*grid*/ pen gs=linewidth(0.7)+cqcqcq+linetype("2 2"); real gx=1,gy=1;
for(real i=ceil(xmin/gx)*gx;i<=floor(xmax/gx)*gx;i+=gx) draw((i,ymin)--(i,ymax),gs); for(real i=ceil(ymin/gy)*gy;i<=floor(ymax/gy)*gy;i+=gy) draw((xmin,i)--(xmax,i),gs);

Label laxis; laxis.p=fontsize(10);

xaxis("",xmin,xmax,Ticks(laxis,Step=1.0,Size=2,NoZero),Arrows(6),above=true); yaxis("",ymin,ymax,Ticks(laxis,Step=1.0,Size=2,NoZero),Arrows(6),above=true);
real f1(real x){return 1-sqrt(1-x^2);} draw(graph(f1,-1,1),linewidth(1.2));
real f2(real x){return sqrt(2*x-x^2);} draw(graph(f2,0,2),linewidth(1.2));
real f3(real x){return -sqrt(2*x-x^2);} draw(graph(f3,0,2),linewidth(1.2));

clip((xmin,ymin)--(xmin,ymax)--(xmax,ymax)--(xmax,ymin)--cycle);

[/asy]

The enclosed region is the region between the graphs of $y=\sqrt{2x-x^2}$ and $y=1-\sqrt{1-x^2}$ from $x=0$ to $x=1$.  The area of this region is

$$\int_0^1 (\sqrt{2x-x^2}-(1-\sqrt{1-x^2}))\,dx=\int_0^1 (\sqrt{2x-x^2}+\sqrt{1-x^2}-1)\,dx.$$We can evaluate this integral using the substitution $x=\sin t$, $dx=\cos t\,dt$.  Then
\begin{align*}
\int_0^1 (\sqrt{2x-x^2}+\sqrt{1-x^2}-1)\,dx&=\int_0^{\pi/2} (\sqrt{2\sin t-\sin^2 t}+\sqrt{1-\sin^2 t}-1)\cos t\,dt\\
&=\int_0^{\pi/2} (\sqrt{\sin t(2-\sin t)}+\cos t-1)\cos t\,dt\\
&=\int_0^{\pi/2} (\sqrt{\sin t(2-\sin t)}\cos t+\cos^2 t-\cos t)\,dt\\
&=\int_0^{\pi/2} (\sqrt{\sin t(2-\sin t)}\cos t+\frac{1+\cos 2t}{2}-\cos t)\,dt.
\end{align*}The integral $\int_0^{\pi/2} \sqrt{\sin t(2-\sin t)}\cos t\,dt$ can be evaluated using the substitution $u=\sin t$, $du=\cos t\,dt$, to get
\[\int_0^1 \sqrt{u(2-u)}\,du.\]Then
\[\int_0^1 \sqrt{u(2-u)}\,du=\int_0^1 \sqrt{2u-u^2}\,du=\int_0^1 \sqrt{1-(u-1)^2}\,du.\]This integral represents the area of a quarter-circle of radius 1, so it equals $\frac{\pi}{4}$.  Therefore, the area of the enclosed region is
\[\frac{\pi}{4}+\frac{1}{2}\left[\frac{t}{2}+\frac{\sin 2t}{4}\right]_0^{\pi/2}-\left[\sin t\right]_0^{\pi/2}=\frac{\pi}{4}+\frac{\pi}{8}-1=\boxed{\frac{3\pi}{8}-1}.\]

